description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited for a 6-month post as a Registrar in Dermatology (Senior Clinical Fellow, ST3+ grade), to start as soon as possible, at Whittington Health NHS Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post will be ideal for a junior doctor who has completed core training and who would like to enter specialist training in Dermatology. This post has been previously approved by the deanery for training.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whittington Health NHS Trust provides comprehensive on-site Dermatology services, including a full range of outpatient services (eg. Phototherapy, Photodynamic Therapy, Ionotophoresis) One –stop skin cancer clinics, Paediatric Dermatology service, Vulval, Bullous and inpatient beds . There will be opportunities to do skin surgery, audit, teach undergraduates and get involved in research.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working alongside six dynamic Consultant Dermatologists, a dermatology registrar, a GPVTS junior doctor and two specialist nurses you will have the opportunity to learn and develop your Dermatology skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is no out of hours commitment and there maybe opportunity to extend the post. The post will have the added advantage of being involved in Clinical Research as we are currently actively recruiting to a number of clinical trials.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suitable applicants ideally will have previous experience in the management of dermatology patients, and a broad knowledge of general medicine. Applicants must have full GMC registration and ideally have MRCP (UK) or equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Chris DohuvicJob titleConsultant DermatologistEmail addresschris.duhovic@nhs.netAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information about this post, please contact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dr Chris Dohuvic, Consultant Dermatologist and Clinical Lead&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;chris.duhovic@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
